{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:04:21.702102+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "## Summary: Running, Building & Previewing the React Admin App\n\nThis is a **Vite + React + TypeScript + MUI** admin template (package name: `vite-react-ts-admin`). Below are the key workflows.\n\n---\n\n### 🔧 1. Local Development\n\n**Prerequisites:** Node.js (LTS), Yarn\n\n```bash\n# 1. Copy the local environment file\ncp envs/.env.local .env\n\n# 2. Install dependencies\nyarn install\n\n# 3. Start the dev server (hot-reload, accessible on your network via --host)\nyarn dev\n```\nThe dev server runs at `http://localhost:10086` (port defined by `VITE_PORT` in `envs/.env.local`). The app uses `cross-env NODE_ENV=local` and loads the matching env file automatically via the Vite config (fallback: `envs/.env.local`).\n\n**Staging local dev:**\n```bash\nyarn dev:stg\n```\nThis runs with `NODE_ENV=stg`, loading `envs/.env.stg`.\n\n---\n\n### 🏗️ 2. Building for Different Environments\n\n| Command | Mode | Loaded Env File | Purpose |\n|---------|------|----------------|---------|\n| `yarn build` | `prod` | `envs/.env.local` (since `NODE_ENV` not set, the fallback `NODE_ENV` = `local` actually uses the local env – but the `--mode` flag is `prod`) | Default production build |\n| `yarn build:prod` | `production` | `envs/.env.prod` | Production build for live domain |\n| `yarn build:stg` | `test` | `envs/.env.stg` | Staging/pre‑production build |\n\nAll builds output to the `dist` directory (or the value of `VITE_OUTPUT_DIR`).\n\n> **Note on Vite mode:** The `--mode` flag sets `import.meta.env.MODE`. The actual `.env` file loaded is determined by the `dotenv` config in `vite.config.ts`, which checks `NODE_ENV` (set by `cross-env`). The commands use `cross-env` to set `NODE_ENV`, which then loads the correct file from `envs/`.\n\n---\n\n### 🖥️ 3. Previewing a Build Locally\n\nAfter building (e.g., `yarn build:prod`), preview the production bundle with:\n\n```bash\nyarn serve\n```\nThis runs `vite preview --host`, serving the built `dist` folder on a local server.\n\n---\n\n### 🐳 4. Docker Deployment\n\nA two‑stage `Dockerfile` is provided:\n\n1. **Build stage** – installs deps and runs `yarn build` (which uses the default `prod` mode).\n2. **Nginx stage** – copies the built `dist` folder into `/usr/share/nginx/html` and applies the custom `nginx.conf`.\n\n```bash\n# Build the image\ndocker build -t react-admin .\n\n# Run it\ndocker run -p 80:80 react-admin\n```\n\nThe `nginx.conf` enables gzip, serves the SPA (with `try_files` fallback to `index.html`), and also supports a `/admin` sub‑path alias.\n\n---\n\n### ☁️ 5. Netlify Deployment\n\nA minimal `netlify.toml` provides a catch‑all redirect rule for client‑side routing:\n\n```toml\n[[redirects]]\n  from = \"/*\"\n  to = \"/\"\n  status = 200\n```\n\nThis ensures all paths (e.g., `/dashboard`, `/user`) return `index.html` so React Router can handle them.\n\n---\n\n### 📦 Other Utilities\n\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `yarn lint` | Run ESLint across `.jsx/.js/.ts/.tsx` files |\n| `yarn fix` | Auto‑fix lint issues (ESLint `--fix`) |\n| `yarn deploy` | Publish the `dist` folder to GitHub Pages via `gh-pages` |\n\nThe repo also uses **Taskfile** (`Taskfile.yaml`) with helper tasks like `task init` (copies `.env.local` and installs deps) and `task release` (standard-version + changelog).\n\n---\n\n### 📁 Environment File Summary\n\n| File | `NODE_ENV` | `VITE_BUILD_ENV` | API Base URL | Port |\n|------|------------|------------------|--------------|------|\n| `envs/.env.local` | `local` | `development` | `https://mock.local.lantron.ltd` | `10086` |\n| `envs/.env.stg` | `stg` | `production` | `https://mock.stg.lantron.ltd` | `10086` |\n| `envs/.env.prod` | `prod` | `production` | `https://mock.lantron.ltd` | *(none)* |\n\nThe Vite config first looks for a `.env` file in the project root; if missing, it falls back to `envs/.env.${NODE_ENV}`.", "additional_kwargs": 